comments:
Created 1894 from the parts in Abingdon Municipal Borough of the 
    parishes of St. Helen, St. Nicholas, Sutton Wick and Culham.
Abolished 1.4.1900 and added to the parish of Radley.

Abolished 1.4.1926 and added to the parish of St. Giles & 
    St. John. See also Table 2, notes (f) and (g).
Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Clifton Hampden.
Abolished 1.4.1900 and added to the parish of Radley.
Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Stadhampton.
See Table 2, note (h).

In 1894 the part in Berkshire  became part 
    of the parish of Abingdon, so that thereafter Culham was wholly in Oxfordshire. 
    See also Table 2, note (h).

Abolished 1.4.1971 and added to the parish of Kingston Bagpuize 
    with Southmoor.
See Table 2, note (h).
Abolished 1.4.1952 and added to the parish of Fyfield & Tubney.
Created 1.4.1952 from the parishes of Fyfield and Tubney.
Created 1.4.1936 out of the parishes of Radley and South Hinksey.

Abolished 1.4.1971 and added to the parish of Kingston Bagpuize 
    with Southmoor.

Created 1.4.1971 from the parishes of Kingston Bagpuize and Draycot 
    Moor.
See Table 2, note (a).
See Table 2, note (h).

In 1889 the part of the parish of South Hinksey in Oxford County 
    Borough became part of Oxfordshire. In 1894 this area became part of the parish 
    of St. Thomas, so that thereafter North Hinksey was again wholly in Berkshire. 
    See also Table 2, notes (c) and (e).
See Table 2, note (h).
See Table 2, note (h).

In 1889 the part of the parish of Seacourt in Oxford County Borough 
    became part of Oxfordshire. In 1894 this area became a separate parish under 
    the provisions of the Local Government Act, 1894 and thereafter Seacourt was 
    again wholly in Berkshire. Abolished 1.4.1900 and added to the parish of 
    Wytham.

In 1889 the part of the parish of South Hinksey in Oxford County 
    Borough became part of Oxfordshire. In 1894 this area became part of the parish 
    of St. Aldate, so that thereafter South Hinksey was again wholly in Berkshire. 
    See also Table 2, notes (b), (c) and (e).

That part which until 1894 formed the part of the parish of 
    South Hinksey in Oxford County Borough. See also Table 2, notes (c) and (e).

Abolished 1894 and divided between the parishes of Abingdon and 
    St. Helen Without.

Created 1894 from the rural parts of the parishes of St. Helen 
    and St. Nicholas.

Abolished 1894 to become the separate parishes of Abingdon and 
    St. Helen Without.

That part which until 1894 formed the part of the parish of 
    North Hinksey in Oxford County Borough. See also Table 2, note (c).
See Table 2, note (h).
See Table 2, note (d).

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Drayton, 
    Abingdon and Sutton Courtenay.
See Table 2, note (h).
Abolished 1.4.1952 and added to the parish of Fyfield & Tubney.

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Seacourt in Oxford 
    County Borough, which became a separate parish under the provisions of the Local 
    Government Act, 1894. Abolished 1.4.1929 and added to the parish of St. 
    Giles & St. John.
